cast.original_title: Tinker Bell and the Pirate Fairy
cast.overview: Zarina, a smart and ambitious dust-keeper fairy who’s captivated by Blue Pixie Dust and its endless possibilities, flees Pixie Hollow and joins forces with the scheming pirates of Skull Rock, who make her captain of their ship. Tinker Bell and her friends must embark on an epic adventure to find Zarina, and together they go sword-to-sword with the band of pirates led by a cabin boy named James, who’ll soon be known as Captain Hook himself.
cast.title: Tinker Bell and the Pirate Fairy

cast.overview: Jaded 74-year-old lizard Leo has been stuck in the same Florida classroom for decades with his terrarium-mate turtle. When he learns he only has one year left to live, he plans to escape to experience life on the outside but instead gets caught up in the problems of his anxious students — including an impossibly mean substitute teacher.
cast.title: Leo

cast.overview: A fading celebrity decides to use a black market drug, a cell-replicating substance that temporarily creates a younger, better version of herself.
cast.title: The Substance

details.biography:
Chase Fein is an American actor, born in New York City and raised in New Jersey.

After studying drama at the Tisch School at New York University (Stella Adler) he completed his Masters in Classical Acting from Central Saint Martin while living in London and Moscow, working at both The Globe Theater and Boris Shchukin Theater Institute respectively. During his time at NYU he lived in London for a semester, studying at The Royal Academy of Dramatic Art.

Chase currently lives in Los Angeles, California
details.name: Chase Fein
